# AI Section Library — Architecture & Conventions

## Core Pattern: Select + Inject, Not Generate

Instead of generating 500+ lines of SDUI JSON from scratch (error-prone, slow), the section library stores pre-validated JSON variants. The AI's only job is:
1. Pick a `variantId` from the manifest
2. Fill a small set of `[[SLOT_NAME]]` values (optional, most have defaults)

```typescript
// AI output (compact — ~100 tokens)
{ variantId: "hero.overlay-centered", params: { CTA_PATH: "/shop" } }

// SectionLibrary assembles the full SDUI node (pre-validated, instant)
const node = sectionLibrary.instantiate("hero.overlay-centered", { CTA_PATH: "/shop" });
```

## File Structure

```
lib/ai/section-library/
  types.ts              — shared types (SectionVariant, SlotName, ManifestEntry, etc.)
