## Slot Syntax

- `[[SLOT_NAME]]` in variant JSON strings = replaced at instantiation time
- `{{state.path}}` in variant JSON strings = SDUI runtime interpolation (NOT replaced by library)
- Most variants have only optional slots with sensible defaults
- Required slots (if any) are listed in `_meta.requiredSlots`

**Common slots:**
- `[[CTA_PATH]]` — navigation destination (default: `/shop`)
- `[[SECTION_TITLE]]` — section heading (default varies per section)
- `[[HEADLINE]]` — for press/awards sections

## Anchor ID Convention

Every key node in a section variant carries a stable `id` attribute for element-level editing. This is the anchor the edit system uses to find nodes for Tier 1 and Tier 2 edits.

**Standard anchor IDs per section type:**

```
Hero:         hero-section, hero-heading, hero-subheading, hero-image, hero-cta-primary
Product Grid: product-grid-section, product-grid-title, product-grid-view-all, product-card
Carousel:     product-carousel-section, carousel-title, carousel-card
Categories:   categories-section, categories-title, category-card
Newsletter:   newsletter-section, newsletter-heading, newsletter-input, newsletter-submit
Testimonials: testimonials-section, testimonials-title, testimonial-card, testimonial-review
Features:     features-section, feature-item-0, feature-item-1, feature-item-2
Brand Story:  brand-story-section, brand-story-heading, brand-story-body, brand-story-image
Flash Sale:   flash-sale-section, flash-sale-title, flash-sale-timer
Navbar:       navbar-root, navbar-inner, navbar-left, navbar-right, navbar-cart, navbar-auth
```

**When adding a new variant:** Tag these key elements with `id` attributes:
- Section root node
- Main heading
- Primary image (if any)
- Primary CTA button
- Each repeated item card

## 4-Tier Edit System

When a user requests a UI change, route to the cheapest possible operation:

| Tier | Name | Trigger | Time | AI? |
|------|------|---------|------|-----|
| 1 | StyleInterpreter | Color, padding, text, remove, show/hide | <100ms | No |
| 2 | EditAgent | Add dropdown, change actions, add element | 1-2s | Micro-AI on subtree only |
| 3 | Section Swap | "Change hero layout", "use horizontal grid" | <100ms | No |
| 4 | Full Regen | New page, new section type | 10-15s | Full pipeline |

### Tier 1 examples (auto-detected by regex):
- "make it blue" → `!bg-blue-500` on className
- "more padding" → bump padding class
- "remove this" → delete node from parent
- "change text to X" → update `text` field
- "make it bold" → add `font-bold`
- "rounded corners" → add `rounded-xl`

### Tier 2 examples (EditAgent sees only 5-40 lines):
- "add a dropdown to the navbar" → EditAgent sees navbar subtree only
- "when I click this, open cart" → EditAgent sees button's `actions` object (5 lines)
- "add a badge that says SALE" → EditAgent sees hero subtree (40 lines)

### Tier 3 examples (SectionLibrary.instantiate(), no AI):
- "swap to horizontal product grid" → `sectionLibrary.instantiate("product-grid.horizontal", existingParams)`
- "use the minimal newsletter" → `sectionLibrary.instantiate("newsletter.minimal", {})`

## How to Add a New Section Variant

1. Create or update a file in `lib/ai/section-library/variants/`
2. Export a `SectionVariant` object with `_meta` and `node`
3. Register it in `lib/ai/section-library/index.ts` ALL_VARIANTS array
4. Add a compact `ManifestEntry` to `lib/ai/section-library/manifest.ts`
5. Tag key elements with stable anchor IDs

## SectionLibrary API

```typescript
import { sectionLibrary } from '@/lib/ai/section-library';

// Get all variants for a section type
const heroVariants = sectionLibrary.getVariants('hero');

// Instantiate a variant with slots filled
const node = sectionLibrary.instantiate('hero.overlay-centered', { CTA_PATH: '/collection' });

// Collect all initActions needed for a page
const actions = sectionLibrary.collectInitActions(['hero.overlay-centered', 'product-grid.4col']);
// Returns: ['fetchNewArrivals'] (hero needs no initActions)
```

## SectionCustomizer API

```typescript
import { sectionCustomizer } from '@/lib/ai/section-library/customizer';

// Swap section at index 2 with a new variant
const updated = sectionCustomizer.swapSection(page, {
  sectionIndex: 2,
  newVariantId: 'product-grid.horizontal',
  params: { SECTION_TITLE: 'Shop All' },
});

// Apply a Tier 2 AI patch (from EditAgent)
const patched = sectionCustomizer.applySubtreeEdit(page, {
  nodePath: 'content.children[0]',
  updatedSubtree: editAgentOutput.patchedSubtree,
});
```

## Rules

1. **NEVER generate SDUI JSON from scratch for content sections** when a library variant exists. Always check the manifest first.
2. **Always use [[SLOT_NAME]] for library slots**, never `{{state.path}}` (that's SDUI runtime interpolation).
3. **Always add anchor IDs to key nodes** when creating new variants.
4. **Tier 2 edits must use minimal subtrees** — extract with `extractEditableSubtree()`, not the full page.
5. **Validate before applying** — call `validateSubtree()` from `edit-agent.ts` before splicing in an EditAgent result.
